Port Authority: Labor Relations Instructions. Promulgated by the PA in 1970, the LRI provided for an unilateral panel to hear labor disputes. Internal hearings held by the PA Commission heard the objections of the several PA unions. Further objections were taken to the state level (including the Public Employment Relations Board; State senate bills 8810 and 8973 in 1972). In 1976, an "independent" panel (the PA Employment Relations Board) was established by law to replace the LRI panel. Records include documents of the internal and state hearings, bills, correspondence from the unions, drafts of the proposed labor instructions, procedures for representation, precedents, testimonies by Local 66, AFL-CIO legislative pamphlets, Joint Gubernatorial Committee reports, resumes for selection of panelists for the new PA Employment Relations Board., 1965-1977
